## Implementation Details

### Layout: `apps/dashboard/src/app/projects/[id]/layout.tsx`

Convert to a client component that fetches project data and provides interactive tab navigation.

**Responsibilities:**
1. Extract `id` from the URL via `useParams()`.
2. Fetch project details via `useSWR` calling `GET /api/projects/${id}`.
3. Display the project header (name, GitHub repo, status).
4. Render tab navigation with `<Link>` components and active state detection.
5. Render children (the page content).

```typescript
"use client";

import { useParams, usePathname } from "next/navigation";
import Link from "next/link";
import useSWR from "swr";
import { fetcher } from "@/lib/swr";
import { StatusBadge } from "@/components/projects/status-badge";

export default function ProjectLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const params = useParams();
  const pathname = usePathname();
  const id = params.id as string;

  const { data: project, error, isLoading } = useSWR(`/api/projects/${id}`, fetcher);

  const tabs = [
    { name: "Overview", href: `/projects/${id}` },
    { name: "Deployments", href: `/projects/${id}/deployments` },
    { name: "Environment", href: `/projects/${id}/environment` },
    { name: "Settings", href: `/projects/${id}/settings` },
  ];

  function isActiveTab(href: string): boolean {
    if (href === `/projects/${id}`) {
      return pathname === href;
    }
    return pathname.startsWith(href);
  }

  if (isLoading) {
    return <ProjectLayoutSkeleton />;
  }

  if (error || !project) {
    return <ProjectNotFound />;
  }

  return (
    <div>
      {/* Project Header */}
      <div className="mb-6">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
          <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">{project.name}</h2>
          {project.recentDeployments?.[0] && (
            <StatusBadge status={project.recentDeployments[0].status} />
          )}
        </div>
        {project.githubRepoFullName && (
          <a
            href={`https://github.com/${project.githubRepoFullName}`}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            className="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-700"
          >
            {project.githubRepoFullName}
          </a>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* Tab Navigation */}
      <div className="mb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
        <nav className="-mb-px flex gap-6">
          {tabs.map((tab) => (
            <Link
              key={tab.href}
              href={tab.href}
              className={`border-b-2 pb-3 text-sm font-medium transition-colors ${
                isActiveTab(tab.href)
                  ? "border-gray-900 text-gray-900"
                  : "border-transparent text-gray-500 hover:border-gray-300 hover:text-gray-700"
              }`}
            >
              {tab.name}
            </Link>
          ))}
        </nav>
      </div>

      {/* Page Content */}
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Tab active state logic:**
- The "Overview" tab is active only when the pathname is exactly `/projects/:id`.
- All other tabs are active when the pathname starts with their `href` (e.g., `/projects/:id/deployments` and `/projects/:id/deployments/abc123` both activate the "Deployments" tab).

### Page: `apps/dashboard/src/app/projects/[id]/page.tsx`

The project overview page. Converts to a client component that uses the project data from the SWR cache (or fetches its own).

**Layout:**

```
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                    |
| Production URL                                                     |
| https://my-app.yourdomain.dev  [open link icon]                   |
|                                                                    |
+------------------------------------------------------------------+

+------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Quick Actions                                                      |
|                                                                    |
| [ Deploy ]   [ View Logs ]                                        |
+------------------------------------------------------------------+

+------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Recent Deployments                                                 |
|                                                                    |
| [ready]  a1b2c3d  main    2 hours ago    34s                      |
| [failed] e5f6g7h  main    5 hours ago    12s                      |
| [ready]  i9j0k1l  main    1 day ago      45s                     |
| [ready]  m3n4o5p  main    2 days ago     38s                     |
| [ready]  q7r8s9t  main    3 days ago     41s                     |
|                                                                    |
| View all deployments →                                            |
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

**Sections:**

#### 1. Production URL Section
- Show the current production URL from the latest `ready` deployment.
- URL is clickable and opens in a new tab.
- If no production deployment exists, show "No production deployment yet."

#### 2. Quick Actions Section
- **Deploy button:** Triggers `POST /api/projects/:id/deployments` with empty body (defaults to production branch).
  - On click: show a confirmation dialog ("Deploy from main branch?")
  - On confirm: send POST, show loading state, navigate to the deployment detail page on success
  - On error: show error toast
- **View Logs button:** Links to the latest deployment's detail page (`/projects/:id/deployments/:latestDeploymentId`).
  - Disabled if no deployments exist.

#### 3. Recent Deployments Section
- Show the 5 most recent deployments (from `project.recentDeployments` returned by the GET API).
- Each row shows:
  - Status badge (from StatusBadge component)
  - Commit SHA (first 7 characters, monospace font)
  - Branch name
  - Relative timestamp ("2 hours ago")
  - Build duration (formatted as seconds, e.g., "34s")
- Each row is clickable, navigates to `/projects/:id/deployments/:deploymentId`.
- "View all deployments" link at the bottom navigates to `/projects/:id/deployments`.

